    "subject": "Mathematics",
    "topic": "trigonometric-series",
    "difficulty": "medium",
    "solution": "<p>$$\\begin{aligned}\n&\\begin{aligned}\n& \\frac{1}{\\sin \\frac{\\pi}{6}} \\sum_{r=1}^{13} \\frac{\\sin \\left[\\left(\\frac{\\pi}{4}+\\frac{\\mathrm{r} \\pi}{6}\\right)-\\left(\\frac{\\pi}{4}\\right)-(\\mathrm{r}-1) \\frac{\\pi}{6}\\right]}{\\sin \\left(\\frac{\\pi}{4}+(\\mathrm{r}-1) \\frac{\\pi}{6}\\right) \\sin \\left(\\frac{\\pi}{4}+\\frac{\\mathrm{r} \\pi}{6}\\right)} \\\\\n& \\frac{1}{\\sin \\frac{\\pi}{6}} \\sum_{\\mathrm{r}=1}^{13}\\left(\\cot \\left(\\frac{\\pi}{4}+(\\mathrm{r}-1) \\frac{\\pi}{6}\\right)-\\cot \\left(\\frac{\\pi}{4}+\\frac{\\mathrm{r} \\pi}{6}\\right)\\right) \\\\\n& =2 \\sqrt{3}-2=\\alpha \\sqrt{3}+\\mathrm{b}\n\\end{aligned}\\\\\n&\\text { So } \\mathrm{a}^2+\\mathrm{b}^2=8\n\\end{aligned}$$</p>",
